1
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:44,040
I want to drive trucks because

2
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:45,000
every time I set out,

3
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,040
I get to go somewhere different

4
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:46,959
and see different scenery.

5
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:48,840
But I think

6
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,239
from what your parents want,

7
00:01:50,519 --> 00:01:51,840
a boat captain or the mahjong parlor,

8
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,200
you have to inherit one of them.

9
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,519
That's the fallback they left me.

10
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,879
Actually,

11
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,640
fishermen all hope their children

12
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,400
can come back to shore.
Take my dad, for example.

13
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,680
My dad is like a shark.

14
00:02:01,879 --> 00:02:03,000
He loves thrashing around in the sea.

15
00:02:03,599 --> 00:02:04,719
I'm a wild dog.

16
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:05,319
So I have to...

17
00:02:05,319 --> 00:02:06,879
I have to run wild on the road.

18
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,120
Is that a dog bark?

19
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,120
That's a wolf.
I... I'm a wild wolf.

20
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:12,759
I'm a wild wolf. A wild wolf.
Who

21
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,840
calls himself a wild dog?

22
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:15,599
Slip of the tongue.

23
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:16,960
Qing Ye.

24
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:18,120
What do you want to do in the future?

25
00:02:21,599 --> 00:02:22,280
I want to make money.

26
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,120
Pretty direct.

27
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:25,039
Just money?
Nothing else? Yes.

28
00:02:27,039 --> 00:02:27,719
That's pretty shallow.

29
00:02:28,639 --> 00:02:29,560
It's practical.

30
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:30,439
Once I make money,
I can do

31
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,680
what I want to do.

32
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,400
Money gives me security.

33
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:35,919
And I can protect my family

34
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:36,560
from storms.

35
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:38,520
What about you?

36
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:39,919
Do you have any goals?

37
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:40,759
Me?

38
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,199
No.

39
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:44,599
No dreams?

40
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,199
I used to want to be a pilot.

41
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:48,360
And now?

42
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:49,639
Not anymore.

43
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,120
People without dreams

44
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,240
can still live good lives.

45
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,039
Don't keep grilling Wu.

46
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:56,960
Compared to Wu,
we want to know more about you.

47
00:02:59,000 --> 00:02:59,680
What about me?

48
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:01,960
For example,

49
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,080
girls like you

50
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,159
from the city.

51
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:05,639
What kind of boys do you like?

52
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,879
What are you doing?
I mean,

53
00:03:10,199 --> 00:03:12,280
by "like,"

54
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,680
I mean admire,

55
00:03:14,759 --> 00:03:16,080
respect, look up to.

56
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,240
You're reading too much into it.

57
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,199
Well,

58
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:21,400
I like

59
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,319
boys with good grades.

60
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,280
Then I'm out, huh?

61
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,400
Go look at yourself by the sea.

62
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,639
Wash your face and come back.

63
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,639
If I start working hard now,

64
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,479
is there still time?

65
00:03:32,599 --> 00:03:33,560
Why ask me?

66
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:34,840
You took two years off school.

67
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,039
We're about the same level.

68
00:03:36,439 --> 00:03:37,360
Then it's too late.

69
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,520
Of course it's not too late.

70
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,360
When it comes to studying,

71
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,759
as long as you want to start,

72
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,800
it's never too late.

73
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,319
Then let's work hard and try.

74
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,039
Come on.
Come on. Another toast.

75
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,080
Good luck to you.
Kyle! Kyle Hao!

76
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,199
Come on.

77
00:03:55,439 --> 00:03:58,159
You really will succeed.

78
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:04,759
You're up so early.

79
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:07,879
I couldn't sleep.

80
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,240
What about you?

81
00:06:10,079 --> 00:06:11,279
Up this early to watch the sea?

82
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,519
I couldn't sleep either.

83
00:06:14,639 --> 00:06:16,000
I came out for a walk

84
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:17,600
and to think about some things.

85
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,519
What things?

86
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:21,800
Yesterday you asked me

87
00:06:22,279 --> 00:06:23,120
if I had a dream.

88
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,720
I said no.

89
00:06:25,839 --> 00:06:26,680
Actually, it's not that I don't.

90
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,680
I just haven't figured it out yet.

91
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:34,279
If you haven't, take your time.

92
00:06:34,839 --> 00:06:35,800
Like you said,

93
00:06:36,199 --> 00:06:37,680
some people don't have dreams

94
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,279
and still live well, don't they?

95
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,639
But there's one thing

96
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,240
I've figured out.

97
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:45,360
What?

98
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:47,920
I want to go to college.

99
00:06:53,759 --> 00:06:54,680
College?

100
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,839
That's it?

101
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:00,319
College

102
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,120
can't be a bad choice.

103
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,560
Why

104
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,319
did you suddenly make up your mind?

105
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:13,839
Because

106
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:24,240
I want to try

107
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:25,920
what it feels like to be a good student.

108
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,519
See? I told you.

109
00:08:09,759 --> 00:08:12,399
What parent wouldn't agree

110
00:08:12,399 --> 00:08:13,600
when a kid wants to go back to school?

111
00:08:13,959 --> 00:08:15,439
Besides, I saw her dad's

112
00:08:15,439 --> 00:08:16,439
condition too.

113
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,439
He isn't someone

114
00:08:17,439 --> 00:08:18,879
who can't be reasoned with.

115
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:20,199
Exactly.
Just as I expected.

116
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:22,920
Unlike our Wu.

117
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,639
To get him back to school,

118
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,680
you have to beg him.

119
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,720
Good thing

120
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:28,600
Qing Ye stepped in herself.

121
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:29,319
Grandma.

122
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,600
Your favorite sea urchin egg custard.

123
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,320
You eat first. Okay.
See?

124
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,000
My grandson is still the most filial.

125
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,679
Here, Mom. Have some soup.

126
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,879
Okay. Thank you. Thank you.

127
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:39,600
Ye.

128
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,679
I heard you're forming

129
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,000
with Shi Min

130
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,919
some kind of study group

131
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:46,279
or study squad?

132
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,919
Just a study group.

133
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:50,320
Since everyone needs to study,

134
00:08:50,519 --> 00:08:51,279
we might as well get together

135
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,519
and help each other.

136
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,759
Then what about Wu?

137
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,399
I'll join when I have time.

138
00:08:57,879 --> 00:08:58,879
He's so good already.

139
00:08:58,879 --> 00:09:00,600
At his level, he can study on his own.

140
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:01,519
No way.

141
00:09:01,799 --> 00:09:02,879
I've been out of school so long.

142
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,000
If I have questions,

143
00:09:04,279 --> 00:09:05,320
I still need to ask

144
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,960
Zhazhating's outstanding educator,

145
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:07,960
Teacher Qing Ye.

146
00:09:10,559 --> 00:09:11,679
Wu, since when

147
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,200
did you get so good with words?

148
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:14,879
I've learned by watching Teacher Qing Ye.

149
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,840
Here, have some egg.

150
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:19,360
Study hard, ask questions, keep at it.

151
00:09:19,519 --> 00:09:20,360
From now on,

152
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,960
study hard with Teacher Qing Ye.

153
00:09:23,799 --> 00:09:24,320
Teacher Qing Ye.
You're too kind. Too kind.

154
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:25,879
Come on. Try this.
Auntie's scrambled eggs.

155
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:27,519
Thank you.

156
00:09:27,559 --> 00:09:29,159
Teacher Qing Ye.

157
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,240
Teacher Qing Ye, have some fish.

158
00:09:31,679 --> 00:09:32,519
It's good. It's good.

159
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,799
Watch out for bones.

160
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,519
Leave it. I'll do it.

161
00:09:38,919 --> 00:09:39,919
What's hard about washing dishes?

162
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:41,200
I've even shucked oysters.

163
00:09:42,519 --> 00:09:43,759
Aren't you supposed to tutor me?

164
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:45,080
You need to prepare, right?

165
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:47,799
All right.

166
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,879
I'll go prepare the questions.

167
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,759
I'll wait upstairs.

168
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:51,879
Okay. Ten minutes.

169
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,519
Wait.

170
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,600
Give me the apron.

171
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,240
Right, right.

172
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,600
Sis, what are you washing?

173
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,720
Clothes.

174
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,919
You come here to do laundry too?

175
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,679
Yes. I'm collecting towels.

176
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,200
More cardboard boxes piled up.

177
00:10:55,519 --> 00:10:56,840
Those are Zhang's, right?

178
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:58,720
Probably.

179
00:11:00,919 --> 00:11:01,519
Zhang.

180
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,720
Zhang.

181
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,720
What decade is this?

182
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,480
Why keep so many cardboard boxes?

183
00:11:08,519 --> 00:11:09,600
Get rid of them.

184
00:11:10,639 --> 00:11:12,519
They won't sell for much anyway.

185
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:14,080
If you run into

186
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,120
a cigarette butt
or something,

187
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,000
and it starts a fire,
what then?

188
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:19,639
Zhang.

189
00:11:20,039 --> 00:11:20,759
Okay, okay.

190
00:11:20,879 --> 00:11:21,799
I know, Lanfang.

191
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:22,879
Hurry up.

192
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:34,840
What happened to ten minutes?

193
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,240
Washing dishes

194
00:11:36,559 --> 00:11:37,600
and taking off the apron took ten minutes.

195
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,759
I tied it into a knot by accident.

196
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:42,960
Come on.

197
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:44,200
Do the problems.

198
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:46,039
Let's treat it as a placement test.
After this,

199
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,080
we'll practice based on your weak spots.

200
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:49,879
Just start.

201
00:11:51,679 --> 00:11:52,120
Take your time.

202
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,600
I'll stay with you.

203
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:55,679
Okay.

204
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,440
ABCD.

205
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:26,039
The base ABCD is a rhombus.

206
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,759
This side is length four.

207
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,960
And this side is length two.

208
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,039
What you need to prove

209
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,440
is that this line

210
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:36,080
and this inclined plane

211
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:37,720
are parallel.

212
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:38,879
How do we prove that?

213
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:40,600
First, draw an auxiliary line.

214
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,200
Once you prove these two angles

215
00:12:42,559 --> 00:12:43,600
are both ninety degrees,

216
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,360
you prove it's parallel

217
00:12:45,559 --> 00:12:46,519
to this plane.
Right?

218
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:50,639
Right.

219
00:12:50,639 --> 00:12:52,320
Don't look at me. Did you get it?

220
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:53,039
I got it.
Good. You got it.

221
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,879
Apply it to another one. Here.

222
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:56,759
This is similar. Geometry too.

223
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:58,039
Try this one for me.

224
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,159
AA1 equals four.

225
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:01,320
AB2 equals two.

226
00:13:02,679 --> 00:13:04,720
MN is parallel to the plane.

227
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,360
Prove this is parallel to this.

228
00:13:07,919 --> 00:13:08,919
It's not on this plane.

229
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,200
Youth is wonderful.

230
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,720
Learning never ends.

231
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:43,960
Here.

232
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,399
They're still studying?

233
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:46,399
Yes.

234
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:49,679
Study by lamplight through the night,

235
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,399
that's exactly when young men should read.

236
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,039
Can I have some water?

237
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,279
Yes, yes, yes.

238
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,080
Wu is still young.

239
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,960
He has a long road ahead.

240
00:14:00,519 --> 00:14:01,879
He needs to study more

241
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,759
to have a better future.

242
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,919
Yes, yes. Exactly.

243
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,519
We can't always let Wu

244
00:14:07,559 --> 00:14:08,799
worry about this family.

245
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:11,240
Seeing the kids work so hard,

246
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,320
I need to try harder too.

247
00:14:14,279 --> 00:14:14,960
I know.

248
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,559
Xuan Island has been doing well lately.

249
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:19,720
As the boss lady,

250
00:14:20,039 --> 00:14:20,799
you're very successful.

251
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,879
Mom, do you know?

252
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:26,759
Since Xuan Island reopened,

253
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,320
we have way more customers than before.

254
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:30,320
Now everyone knows

255
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:31,759
that I, Li Lanfang,

256
00:14:31,799 --> 00:14:33,279
have all five certificates,

257
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,879
so they feel safer.

258
00:14:36,279 --> 00:14:37,000
So to speak,

259
00:14:37,519 --> 00:14:39,320
even a setback can have a silver lining.

260
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,399
Sometimes bad things

261
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,639
can turn into good things.

262
00:14:42,519 --> 00:14:43,039
Exactly.

263
00:14:43,399 --> 00:14:44,240
I want

264
00:14:44,799 --> 00:14:46,320
to ride this momentum

265
00:14:46,879 --> 00:14:48,559
and expand my hairdressing career.

266
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:52,320
Tell me about it.

267
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:56,000
Recently, I saw online

268
00:14:56,759 --> 00:14:58,519
that the hottest thing now

269
00:14:58,559 --> 00:14:59,720
is updos.

270
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,240
I'm planning

271
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,720
to go learn it.

272
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:16,000
What do you think?
Some parts

273
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,919
of your writing

274
00:15:22,639 --> 00:15:23,320
are hard to follow.

275
00:15:23,919 --> 00:15:25,000
Which ones? Let me see.

276
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:35,159
Your essay is

277
00:15:35,519 --> 00:15:36,559
a little weak.

278
00:15:37,879 --> 00:15:39,120
After all these years,

279
00:15:39,559 --> 00:15:40,960
I've forgotten almost all the words.

280
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,000
My English
wasn't very good before anyway.

281
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,200
Memorizing words is too hard.

282
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:46,519
They know me,
but I don't know them.

283
00:15:50,559 --> 00:15:51,519
Do you know the Ebbinghaus
forgetting curve?

284
00:15:54,159 --> 00:15:54,600
What?

285
00:15:54,919 --> 00:15:56,679
The Ebbinghaus forgetting curve.

286
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:00,320
I think I've heard of it.

287
00:16:00,799 --> 00:16:01,519
It works like this.

288
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,399
The Y-axis here

289
00:16:03,399 --> 00:16:04,840
is the amount remembered.

290
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,159
